An Act establishing a living organ donor tax credit.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 6 of chapter 62 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2020
2 Official Edition is hereby amended by inserting at the end thereof the following subsection:-
3 (a) If an individual donates a qualified life-saving organ of such individual for
4 transplantation into another individual during the taxable year, there shall be allowed as a credit
5 against the tax imposed under this section for the taxable year an amount equal to the sum of:
6 “(1) costs paid by the taxpayer in connection with such transplantation,
7 “(2) travel, lodging, and other logistical expenses,
8 “(3) medical expenses related to donation and follow-up care,
9 “(4) paperwork or legal costs related to donation, and
10 “(5) any lost wages of the individual in connection with such transplantation.
11 and shall not exceed $5,000.
1 of 2

12 (b) “Qualified life-saving organ” shall include the kidney, liver, lung, pancreas, intestine,
13 bone marrow, or any part thereof.
